sec.div: 3.3. In Vitro Chemotactic Effect of LEO
sec.p: The present study evaluated the chemotactic effects of LEO at different concentrations (2, 15, and 150 μg/ml) on leukocyte chemotaxis in vitro. However, LEO did not increase leukocytes chemotaxis in any concentrations when compared to the vehicle (RPMI-1640). The fMLP (10 -6 M) (positive control) induced a significant leukocyte migration (data not shown).
